  "text": "Our results also indicated that low intensity aerobic training was able to restore the ability of capillary selfregulation at rest. In fact, studies with diabetic animals had already suggested that, through stimulating angiogenesis, aerobic training was able to partially restore the capillary diffusion capacity and regional distribution reduced by hyperglycemia [CITATION_1] and losses in capillary perfusion [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
